>about


 "Tenth Plague" is a game set in the Biblical story of the final plague
 used to punish Egypt for keeping the Hebrews as slaves. While the
 story is usually told from the perspective of the victor, this game
 focuses more on the questionable morality of punishing innocents
 (children especially) for crimes they did not commit and could not
 prevent. This game comes with a commentary mode, which gives a little
 more insight into this short game. That mode can be
 activated/deactivated at any time with the command "commentary" or
 simply "com". (It also gives puzzle spoilers, so have caution.)

 The cover art is a high-contrast version of the beautifully sad work
 "The Tenth Plague of Egypt", by Joseph Mallord William Turner (1816),
 engraved by William Say, from the Liber Studiorum. The image is in the
 public domain.

 Many thanks to the beta testers: Russell Glasser, C.E.J. Pacian,
 Baldur Brueckner, Matthew Bunyan, Barry Williams, Sunioc, advicebanana
 and sweetandy. You people rock!

 This is my second IF game, and I look forward to more upbeat stories
 in the future.

 If you have any questions, feel free to email me:
 lynnea.dally@gmail.com
